<a name='event_10861' STYLE='text-decoration:none' href='/recreation/calendar.php?event_id=10861'><font face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif' color='#6D8D38'><b>Evergreen Basic Mountain Bike Skills Part 2</b></font></a></td>

</td></tr><tr><td>
If you've taken Basic Mountain Bike Skills Part 1 this course is for you! You'll learn more about tight-turns, rolling over man-made and natural step downs and getting over obstacles. It's designed for adults of any age and kids 14 and above. We welcome families, individuals and groups. <b>Participation in Basic MTB Skills Part 1 is a prerequisite for this class.</b> If you have questions please email the instructor. <br>
<p>
<p>Some skills we will be covering are tight-turns, wheel lifts and rolling down obstacles.
<p> Plan on 3hrs and we'll wrap things up by 1pm.
<p>This class will be taught by Jerry, Kelly and Gabe.
<p>
<b>Class Rates:</b> $50 for Evergreen members (non-members must purchase an Evergreen membership for an additional $30) An annual family membership is $50. The class sign-up pages will automatically determine the right membership for you.

Group will meet in the clearing at Issaquah Community Center and ride the high school trails up to Grand Ridge and then out to Duthie for a lap of all the XC trails. Ride length will be somewhere between 20-22 miles and 2200-2500 of elevation.
<P>
This ride is appropriate for riders that are strong climbers technical ability is intermediate with most of the technical being at Duthie. Grand Ridge includes some steep descents, switchbacks and climbing on technical terrain. Riders must bring a good light with a burn time of at least 3 hours.
<P>
This ride is part of the Sturdy Bitch Purely Custom Ride Challenge. It is not necessary to participate in the challenge email the ride leader if you are interested in this ride series and earning a Purely Custom Sturdy Bitch headset cap and screw. For details on the challenge click here.

This ride is worth 1 point in the series.
<P>

<P>
Riders are expected to have a bike in good working order and have appropriate tools and equipment to perform reasonable maintenance on the trail. This is a self-supported ride to riders should bring appropriate food and water to stay hydrated and fed.
<P>
Any questions please email the ride leader for additional information. Ride will leave on time or within minutes of ride time posting. Thanks!!
